  New progress was made in forestry, especially in tree 
planting. In 1993, trees were planted on 1.695 million mu of 
land in the province, overfulfilling the task in this regard. 
So the percentage of forest cover continued to increase. 
  An across-the-board increase was achieved in animal 
husbandry production. 


