  All county seats and larger areas in the province could be 
reached by telephone. The total postal and telecommunications 
business in 1993 reached 1.03 billion yuan, a growth of 66.6 
percent over 1992. Of this volume, business operated by the 
central government increased 66.9 percent, reaching 960 million 
yuan; business operated by local governments increased 62.8 
percent, reaching 70 million yuan; international and Hong 
Kong/Macao business increased 70.9 percent, reaching 63.499 
million yuan; and express, special, radio paging, and cellular 
phone business increased more than 70 percent. The development 
of long-distance and urban telephone services accelerated 
noticeably. By the end of 1993, the number of urban households 
with telephones had reached 409,000 and the number of rural 
households with telephones had reached 64,000, a growth of 62.9 
and 36.8 percent respectively over the year before. 
<H5>  5. Domestic Trade and Market Prices </H5>
  In 1993, the supply of consumer goods was ample in Anhui, 
and 
retail sales were steadily growing. The total commodity retail 
sales in the year increased 15.9 percent over the year before, 
reaching 39.17 billion yuan. Retails of consumer goods 
increased 17.8 percent, reaching 33.57 billion yuan; and retails 
of agricultural capital goods increased 5.8 percent, reaching 
5.6 billion yuan. Of all the consumer goods sold through retail 
markets, 16.14 billion yuan of goods were sold in cities, 
registering an increase of 26.9 percent over the year before; 
and 7.6 billion and 9.83 billion yuan of goods were sold in 
counties and subcounty areas, registering an increase of 18.8 
and 4.7 percent respectively over the year before. 
  Retail sales of commodities produced by all types of 
business 
registered growth. Retails by state-owned business grew 8.7 
percent, retails by collectively owned units grew 10.9 percent, 
retails by independent operators grew 32.6 percent; and 
peasants' retails among nonagricultural residents grew by 23 
percent. Sales of various types of consumers goods showed that, 
among edible commodities, sales of grain declined 9.4 percent, 
sales of cooking oil increased 26.6 percent, and sales of eggs 
and aquatic goods respectively increased 190 and 74.4 percent. 
Of clothing, sales of garments increased 11.9 percent; and of 
durable goods, sales of color television sets declined 8 
percent, sales of electric fans declined 13.5 percent, sales of 
washing machines increased 12.1 percent, sales of refrigerators 
increased 16.1 percent, and sales of air conditioners and 
kitchen ventilators increased by a great margin. 
  We have made considerable progress in price reform. In 
1993, the government strengthened price reform, decontrolled 
producer's prices for most steel products and for coal subject 
to the state's unified distribution, raised prices of 
electricity and railway freight transportation, and further 
freed purchasing and selling prices of grains. These policies 
played an important role in changing the relatively low prices 
of basic products and infrastructure facilities and in promoting 
the establishment of market mechanisms. 


